<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-12T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/8–948: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-12T15:00:00-04:00">August 12, 1948—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1166. White House states (urtel 1466, Aug. 9) “that the President never
                            made any statement about military aid to China to Mr. Wellington <pb facs="0147" n="137" xml:id="pg_137"/> Koo. The only comment the
                            President made was one to the effect that he hoped that we would all
                            some day see a strong, united China”. Dept relies on your discretion to
                            effect such correction as you think desirable informally and without
                            publicity.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>